				<h2>Answer</h2>
				<h3>Score ::6</h3>
				<p><p>Use img tags with a custom width attribute. In the example you linked to, I've edited it to do just that. Check the revision history to see what I've done.</p>

<pre><code>&lt;img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/1vIgO.png" width="375"&gt;
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>iPhone 4 5s: 320</li>
<li>iPhone 6 6s: 375</li>
<li>iPhone 6+ 6s+: 540</li>
</ul>

<p>If you resize an image and re-upload it as a suggested edit, I'm likely to  reject and edit  it and use the above instead on the original image. Resizing the image loses detail.</p>

<p>Feel free to use even smaller numbers for side-by-side images (e.g. 300) and add <code>[]()</code> or <code>[][]</code> link formatting around the img element to link  to the full-size image.</p>
